LAGOS  – The Lagos State Government has presented the draft final report on Ijegun-Egba action area Plan, making the sixth successive draft final report of development plans to be presented to stakeholders in the last couple of months. Dr. Idris Salako , the Commissioner for Physical Planning and Urban Development, who spoke recently during the presentation of the report to stakeholders at Oriade Local Council Secretariat ,Satellite, said that the aim of the plan was to address infrastructural needs and development pressures in Ijegun-Egba to facilitate the transformation of the area. He said that the Ijegun-Egba Action Area Plan was part of the nine approved by the administration of Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu to stimulate orderly development of the hinterlands. -Advertisement- Salako who spoke through the Director Development Matters, Tpl. Saheed Animashaun stated that Ijegun- Egba Action Area Plan, covering a period of 10 (Ten) years (2021-2031), was part of Physical Development plans designed as viable instruments guiding physical growth and direction of development across the State. “Furthermore, the plan is envisioned to provide solutions to the Physical Planning Problems of Ijegun- Egba and also to address Perennial Environmental Flooding, Drainage Challenges amongst others” , he said. He reiterated that the plan would unlock the developmental and tourism potentials of the area as well as serve as a catalyst for economic prosperity and enhanced aesthetics of Ijegun-Egba. The Action Area Plan for Ijegun- Egba, a rapidly developing settlement within Oriade Local Council Development Area, covers a land area of 1342.15 hectares. The project consultant, Tpl. Kadiri, speaking on behalf of Kadiri Associates Limited, urged the people of Ijegun- Egba to cooperate for timely delivery of the project.